Next implementations are missing but is required

 1 - install packages
 2 - remove packages
 3 - configure packages
 4 - extract packages for inspection and edition
 5 - query package information from database 

1 .- Install packages
 This funtion will be take a pointer with a file name, then whill be 
 test a file and is ok , the package will be installed. The option for
 The argument for this option is "-i, --install"
 
2 .- Remove packages
 This function will be take a pointer with a package name, make a serch
 on local databse for install test, then delete alll package content.
 The argument for this option is "-r, --remove"
 
3.- Configure packages.
 The same of Remove packages, except taht instead file deletion, the funtion
 will be execute a install files.
 The argument for this option is "-c, --config"
  
4.- Extract Package
 The function take a pointer to a package file and decompress in the 
 same current directory
 The argument for this option is "-e, --extract"
 
5.- Query package
 Query package information to a local database using params (rpm style)
 The primary argument for this option is "-q, --query" , and a second
 argument (charset) is needed. Ej,
 
 vpm -qi - Query all installed packages 


A this time only compress package with given directory is implemented.
